	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Mine works just fine on my non-CIC disabled NES.
<br />
<br />The main advantage you have is that the NES motherboard is really thick compared to NES game boards, so the loose part of the connector doesn't have much trouble making contact with the motherboard. And like rbudrick said, it's really reliable and you can basically insert a game once and it'll work.

		

