	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My favorite method for cleaning the edge connector is to find a bowl with a flat bottom...maybe one that margarine comes in or something (cleaned out thoroughly, of course).  Then, fill the bowl with a bout 3/8 of an inch of rubbing alcohol.  Using a soft-bristled toothbrush, place the dirty edge connector in the bowl and scrub away all the grime.  Let it dry thoroughly and you should be golden.
<br />
<br />-Rob

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


